OL,3,COn-trial son admits he 'should have
OL,4,Cdone more' to help malnourished mother
OL,6,FDuring cross-examination by Iain
OL,7,FSimkin KC, messages exchanged by
OL,8,FHolyoak with a friend in October,
OL,9,F2020, were read in court.
OL,11,F"I think she is depressed and
OL,12,Fmalnourished," Holyoak had said in one.
OL,14,FBy way of explanation he told jurors:
OL,15,F"She hadn't been eating anything."
OL,17,FMr Simkin asked him: "What provisions
OL,18,Fdid you have, with Chris, to make sure
OL,19,Fyour mum was cared for?" asked Mr
OL,20,FSimkin.
