OL,3,COn-trial son admits he 'should have
OL,4,Cdone more' to help malnourished mother
OL,6,FHe said he hadn't detected the smell
OL,7,Fof bodily excretions in her downstairs
OL,8,Fliving area, nor seen any of her
OL,9,Fpressure sores. It was put to Holyoak
OL,10,Fthat neither he nor Morgan made sure
OL,11,Fshe was moved properly from time to
OL,12,Ftime to ensure she didn't develop
OL,13,Fthese sores.
OL,15,F"It hadn't occurred to me to do so,"
OL,16,Fsaid Holyoak. It was suggested by Mr
OL,17,FSimkin that neither he nor Morgan
OL,18,Fensured she was eating enough, and
OL,19,Fthat in October, 2020, Holyoak knew
OL,20,Fshe was malnourished.
